text: "Family killed by the Gods" So Hollywood is still too pussy to acknowledge that Herc killed his family himself, even though it happened because the Gods made him briefly insane. Yeah, way to take away a major inner conflict for your main character which actually is the whole reason for him doing the 12 labors. By the way, why can't Hollywood just make THAT as a movie. The Twelve Labors is the central Herc story and has enough story for an entire movie franchise. Why does it always have to be lame LOTR/Braveheart-copies with massive battles? Correct me if I'm wrong because I'm not THAT knowledgeable about Hercules, but I can't remember any of his stories involving him to be some sort of big army leader. He usually walked around alone or with a small group to go on adventures. I really wish someone would make a really ambitious Hercules movie with a good story and good actors that stays relatively true to the myth, rather than making it just a cheesy action fest. Well at least THIS Hercules looks a thousand times better than the other one earlier this year. At least this one has some aspects of the myth like the Lion, the Boar or the Hydra.

text: This movie was great!! Apart from the inconsistency with the actors' accents (a pet hate of mine), this movie was awesome! There were a whole range of things; humour, action, suspense, a definite sense of nobility and heroism which sometimes you just gotta have, as well as a tear-jerking scene. Good acting (excellent in a few scenes), good casting, excellent costume design, good graphics, well constructed characters and an overall well constructed movie with great use of filmic conventions. I was pleased! :) But yes, to all those reading this, go check it out for yourselves!  P.S.    A particular character I liked was Tydeus. Although he said only one word throughout the entire film, he was the one character who spoke to me the most on a very emotional level! Job well done!!  P.S.S.  This movie trumps the other Hercules movie (starring Kellan Lutz) that came out earlier this year by a long shot!

text: It is everything you expect it to be judging from the trailer and the fact it is a Brett Ratner film. Completely serviceable and disposable adventure action movie with just enough roars, over the top battles and those inspirational war speeches to make it fun. The Rock was very good in his role, he was believable and fun to watch, his crew was alright(Ian Mcshane provided some cheap humour) production values are also good, dialogue can be cheesy at times but it was ok. Plot is your typical ancient god,king,mercenary plot - nothing new or memorable. Movie has a couple of twists - some are predictable, others caught me by surprise and the ending is kinda dumb but acceptable. Still a good rental - 3/5.
